The paper discusses the issue of backdoors in encryption algorithms, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed BEA-1 algorithm is a symmetric encryption system, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the mathematical design of the encryption algorithm, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the implementation and detection of backdoors, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and system and information theory (cs.SI).
